   FLA-FIRES-IMPACT (Miami) _ From homeowners demanding
reimbursement for lodging, to the organizers of a postponed Nascar
race, to the the owner of a Daytona fireworks company who laid off
100 workers because there was no Fourth of July celebration, the
recent fires have cost Florida $500 million. But that amount pales
in comparison with past devastating hurricanes or the wildfires of
the 1980s. While Florida agriculture has not suffered greatly,
other Southern states are suffering crop losses from the cause of
the fires: a regional drought. By Mireya Navarro.
</P>
