<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HATE-CRIMES (Washington) _ Dozens of civic, church and civil
rights groups urge Congress to pass legislation making it a federal
crime to attack someone based on bias against gays, women and
people with disabilities. Federal law already prohibits violence
based on race, color, religion or national origin. By NICOLE TSONG.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-GUNS (Washington) _ President Clinton voices support for
a Senate bill that holds adults criminally responsible if they
permit children easy access to firearms. More than a dozen states
have similar laws, which generally require adults to store guns and
bullets in places that are inaccessible to children. By JOHN C.
HENRY.
</P>
<P>
   FLAG-BURNING (Washington) _ Sen. Orrin Hatch of Utah, chairman
of the Senate Judiciary Committee, says after a hearing on flag
burning that a proposed constitutional amendment banning the
practice will come to a vote this fall. By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-RACE (Washington) _ President Clinton holds his second
televised panel discussion on race, a program that will be
broadcast on PBS stations nationally Thursday night. An earlier
forum on race in sports was broadcast from Houston. By BENNETT
ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   AGENTS-SLAIN (Harlingen, Texas) _ A hearse carrying the body of
U.S. Border Patrol agent Ricardo Salinas, 24, heads to San Antonio
for services later this week. Salinas and his training supervisor,
Susan L. Rodriguez, 28, were among the five people who died Tuesday
in a shooting rampage in South Texas. By DANE SCHILLER.
</P>
<P>
   AGENTS-DOMESTIC (Houston) _ The rage that apparently provoked a
jilted boyfriend to go on a bloody rampage that left five people
dead, including himself, in south Texas on Tuesday is all too
common, family violence experts say. By ALLAN TURNER.
</P>
<P>
   NUCLEAR-WASTE (Austin, Texas) _ Two administrative law judges
recommend against allowing a low-level radioactive waste dump to be
built in West Texas, but the agency responsible for overseeing the
dump says it will move ahead with its plan. By CLAY ROBISON.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SOC-WORLD-CUP (Paris) _ In the World Cup semifinal match,
Croatia and France battle for the right to face defending champion
Brazil in the championship game Sunday. By JOHN P. LOPEZ.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-BRAZIL (Marseilles, France) _ Brazil has been criticized and
nit-picked throughout this World Cup, yet once again the Brazilians
have prevailed on the field and will be playing for their
unprecedented fifth World Cup title Sunday. By JOHN P. LOPEZ.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BEST (St. Louis) _ Sporting the best record in franchise
history at the All-Star break, the Houston Astros are sitting
pretty with a five-game lead in the National League Central as they
prepare to open the second half. But just how good is this Astros
team? Does it rank up there with the 1980 and 1986 teams as the
best in franchise history? By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-CARDS (St. Louis) _ The St. Louis Cardinals were expected to
challenge the Houston Astros for supremacy in the NL Central race,
but injuries and inconsistency have made the Cardinals one of the
biggest disappointments in the league. By JOSEPH DUARTE.
</P>
<P>
   With: BBN-MICKEY
</P>
