(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``l'' lifestyle news file. For questions, contact Jimmy Johnson
at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
SUMMER-FASHION (Los Angeles) _ Someone, somewhere may be wearing a
wool suit, but not you. It's summertime, and you're hula-happy,
going on a surfin' safari, headed for Maui-wowie styles or at least
dreamin' about a weekend in Santa Barbara in clothes that don't
have to go to the dry cleaners. By Barbara De Witt. 
. 
SUNGLASSES-FASHION (Los Angeles) _ Sunglasses do so much more than
shade your eyes from those nasty ultraviolet rays and camera
flashes. It's all about 'tude. Pull on a pair of oversized plastic
shades and you, too, can be a movie star like Sophia Loren in the
'50s. By Barbara De Witt. 
. 

