<TEXT>
<P>
   Longhorns are No. 1 - at least in media guides
</P>
<P>
   By Mark Wangrin
</P>
<P>
   Cox News Service
</P>
<P>
   AUSTIN _ It is no cause for an orange Tower, riotous swarming of
the Drag, parades or gaudy trophies.
</P>
<P>
   But if you're a proud University of Texas alum who needs
something in the athletic program to be proud about, there's this
recent development:
</P>
<P>
   In 1997-98, the Longhorns won six national titles, including a
sweep of the three big men's sports _ football, basketball and
baseball.
</P>
<P>
   For media guides.
</P>
<P>
   When bragging, that last part's on a need-to-know basis.
</P>
<P>
   At its recent convention in Spokane, Wash., the College Sports
Information Directors of America also honored the UT guides for
men's swimming and diving and men's track and field as tops in the
nation. The women's basketball guide cover was also chosen No. 1;
the guide itself No. 2 behind Tennessee.
</P>
<P>
   Of the school's 15 media guides, 11 finished in the top 10
nationally.
</P>
<P>
   It's believed that the Longhorns' sweep of the top three men's
sports was the first ever. Judges, one each from print and
electronic media and one with a graphics background, rate the
guides on content, convenience, organization and appeal.
</P>
<P>
   ``They've become more than a media guide,'' said Mary Elliott,
UT athletic publications director. ``They're also used for
recruiting and marketing. But we still make sure it has everything
the media needs.''
</P>
<P>
   Working with publications specialists Mary Elliott and Donna
Seago on the guides were sports information staffers John Bianco
(football), Dave Saba (men's basketball), Mike Forcucci (baseball),
Mark Olsen (track), Penny Abrahams (swimming) and Barb Kowal
(women's basketball).
</P>
<P>
   In winning the football honors, the Horns nudged past perennial
media guide titan Notre Dame, which has won top honors seven times
in the last 20 years.
</P>
<P>
   Next year's football guide has already been sent to the printer
and will include new sections on year-by-year statistics and a
comprehensive look at All- America halfback Ricky Williams'
records, rankings and stats. The 468-page effort _ up 28 pages from
last year _ is available for $18 at Longhorn Ltd., located on the
first floor of Bellmont Hall, or by calling 471-5583 or (800)
982-2386.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
