<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are 20 variably well-known novels by 20 variably well-known
authors that were adapted into 20 variably well-known movies,
always under new titles. (Three of the films were first made under
their literary titles, but later remakes changed the labels.) Match
the title of the book with the movie derived from it. You pass with
11 correct answers and attain an A with 15 right. Score yourself
one extra point for each correct identification of the works filmed
twice under different titles. Answers are on the opposite page.
</P>
<P>
   The literary titles:
</P>
<P>
   1. ``An American Tragedy'' by Theodore Dreiser
</P>
<P>
   2. ``Before the Fact'' by Francis Iles
</P>
<P>
   3. ``Blind Alley'' by James Warwick
</P>
<P>
   4. ``Blood Brother'' by Elliot Arnold
</P>
<P>
   5. ``Bringing Up the Brass'' by Marty Maher
</P>
<P>
   6. ``Buried Alive'' by Arnold Bennett
</P>
