evidence that a recession sweeping through southeast Asia and Japan
is causing a slowdown in this country. By Kimberly Blanton. 750
words.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-REFORM (Tokyo) _ With polls showing the ruling party
slipping in Sunday's parliamentary elections, an increasingly
desperate Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto offers to cut taxes. By
Indira A.R. Lakshmanan. 750 words. (f and i coding)
</P>
<P>
   WORLDCOM-MCI (Undated) -- Worldcom clears a major antitrust
hurdle in its effort to merge with MCI, as European Union
regulators approve the $46 billion deal. US regulators, who had
worked with their European counterparts, are expected to follow
suit soon. By Joann Muller. 800 words.
</P>
