 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on...Daniel Day-Lewis (``THE BOXER'')
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``My Beautiful Laundrette'': As a bisexual street punk in this
urban romantic comedy from Stephen Frears.
</P>
<P>
   ``A Room With a View'': As Helena Bonham Carter's priggish
fiance.
</P>
<P>
   ``My Left Foot'': An Oscar-winning performance as artist-writer
Christy Brown, born with cerebral palsy.
</P>
<P>
   ``In the Name of the Father'': Slammed in jail with his father
for a terrorist bombing he didn't commit.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Last of the Mohicans'': Running through the woods in a
loincloth in Michael Mann's percussive version of the book.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Crucible'': Warding off accusations of witchcraft in
Nicholas Hytner's beautifully acted version of Arthur Miller's
play.
</P>
