network's Tailwind story retraction. (Kloer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FIRE-ANIMALS _ BUNNELL, Fla. _ The trauma isn't over for the
pets, livestock and wild animals routed by Florida fires. Some are
still out in the smoking woods, cut off from their homes, hiding in
culverts, drainage ditches, under cars or in garbage cans,
disoriented and traumatized. (McLachlin, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TX-INSTITUTIONS _ AUSTIN _ In the past three weeks, three Texas
institutions have had their federal money frozen because of serious
health and safety problems. The three sanctions may signal growing
trouble with Texas' ability to keep free from harm the 5,300
mentally retarded people living in state institutions. (Gamino,
Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
