<P>
   FLAG-BURNING (Washington) _ Sen. Orrin Hatch of Utah, chairman
of the Senate Judiciary Committee, says after a hearing on flag
burning that a proposed constitutional amendment banning the
practice will come to a vote this fall. By JUDY HOLLAND. (Already
filed)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-RACE (Washington) _ In a session that was long on talk
but short on solutions, President Clinton joins in another
discussion on race _ this one focusing heavily on school diversity.
By BENNETT ROTH. (Already filed)
</P>
