u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-AGENTS-KILLED-HNS &LR;      07-08 0642
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AGENTS-KILLED-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GUNMAN ACTED ALONE IN SOUTH TEXAS KILLINGS, OFFICIALS SAY 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (Eds.: a la Texas restaurant is cq) 
 
By JAMES PINKERTON 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HARLINGEN, Texas _ A San Benito construction worker was alone
when he went on a deadly rampage early Tuesday that claimed five
lives, including his own, law enforcement authorities said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Cameron County Sheriff Omar Lucio said it was doubtful any other
suspects will be identified other than Ernest Lane Moore, 25, who
died Tuesday evening in a Harlingen hospital. Authorities initially
suspected two others were with Moore at the time of the first
killings, but interviews with eyewitnesses Wednesday confirmed that
Moore acted alone.
</P>
<P>
   ``At this point, we're feeling more confident there was one
individual, the suspect who was shot, Ernest Moore,'' Lucio said.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, blood bank officials in Harlingen said record numbers
of donors have lined up to replace the large amount of blood
products consumed during attempts to save those injured during the
shootings.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said Moore, armed with an assault weapon, went
looking for his former girlfriend, Julie Cox, early Tuesday in the
small community of Rio Hondo.
</P>
<P>
   Moore shot and seriously wounded Dan Morin, a 22-year-old who
had been dating Cox, and killed Morin's mother, Margarita Flores,
53, and older sister, Delia Morin, 31.
</P>
<P>
   After family members wrested the gun from Moore, he fled to his
home outside San Benito and got another assault weapon and shot and
killed two Border Patrol agents and wounded a sheriff's deputy.
Moore was fatally shot in the exchange, but officers continued to
search the area for several hours in case there were others.
</P>
<P>
   Dan Morin, Delia Morin, a brother and Julie Cox all worked at a
San Benito family restaurant named a la Texas, according to a
statement issued Wednesday by owner Christine Stubbs.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are all deeply saddened at the loss of Delia Morin, who was
an exemplary employee and pleasant co-worker,'' the statement
reads. It said the four workers ``always strive to do their best.''
</P>
<P>
   The statement concluded by saying Stubbs was not informed about
her employees' personal relationships and could not comment on
them.
</P>
<P>
   Morin remained in critical condition Wednesday, and family
members say he was shot four times in the abdomen by Moore.
</P>
<P>
   A joint funeral will be held Friday in San Benito.
</P>
<P>
   Two Border Patrol agents, Ricardo Salinas, 24, and Susan
Rodriguez, 28, were gunned down near Moore's home as they prepared
to begin a search for him in a cornfield. Cameron County sheriff's
Deputy Raul Rodriguez was with the agents and shot in the chest.
Hospital officials said he was improving and upgraded his condition
to stable.
</P>
<P>
   Services were scheduled for Moore on Thursday at a San Benito
cemetery, and on Friday in Harlingen for Border Patrol agent
Rodriguez. Services for Salinas, a San Antonio native, will be held
in that city Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Wilma Delaunay, a hospital service coordinator for the Red
Cross, said scores of blood donors lined up outside Harlingen
offices to give blood to replace more than 75 units used Tuesday on
the shooting victims.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're just coming in and talking about what went on
yesterday, and they want to do their part and give blood,'' she
said.
</P>
<P>
   On Tuesday, 49 units of blood were donated and more than 60 on
Wednesday, greatly exceeding the five or 10 units normally given
each day, Delaunay said.
</P>
<P>
   Among those waiting to donate were Margaret Mertens, a member of
the Sisters of Divine Providence, who works at a refugee shelter in
San Benito.
</P>
<P>
   ``I decided we could give blood, this is one way we can help the
families, and the hospital, which they say is short on blood,'' she
said.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
