<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Speeds top 220 mph in AMS tests
 &HT;    By Kent Mitchell
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA -- One thing is certain now about the upcoming Atlanta
500 Classic, Aug. 27-29. Someone will go faster than 200 mph, and
might even get up to 230 on Atlanta Motor Speedway's 1.54-mile
quad-oval.
</P>
<P>
   Indy Racing League drivers conducted tests at AMS under the
lights for the first time Monday and Tuesday, and Tuesday night,
Tony Stewart turned a lap of 228.505 mph, the fastest by a
new-formula IRL car.
</P>
<P>
   The previous fastest lap of 228.012, also by Stewart, was run at
the True Value 500 last month at Texas Motor Speedway in Fort
Worth.
</P>
<P>
   Stewart set an unofficial track record of 226.406 Monday night
at Atlanta in the Glidden-Menards Special Dallara/
Aurora/Firestone.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had a 30-lap run tonight, and I had a good 227 lap at the
end of that,'' Stewart said. ``I passed high and low all night in
turns 1, 3 and 4. I tell you that the people who don't come and
watch this race are going to miss a great show.''
</P>
<P>
   Kelley Racing teammates Mark Dismore and Scott Sharp were
second- and third-fastest, respectively, with laps of 221.494 and
221.079. Rookie Robby Unser, son of three-time Indianapolis 500
champion Bobby Unser, was fourth-fastest at 218.079 in the
Children's Beverage Group-Team Cheever Dallara/Aurora/Goodyear.
</P>
<P>
   For tickets or more information about the race, call
770-946-4211.
</P>
<P>
   Panoz in Playboy
</P>
<P>
   Team Panoz isn't racing this weekend, but the name still makes
the news: Danny Panoz is in Playboy magazine. Well, his car is,
anyway. The August issue features a half-page photo and article on
page 33 about the Panoz Roadster, built right up the road in
Braselton. It was the younger Panoz's interest in cars that led to
Team Panoz, the Panoz GTR and the purchase of Road Atlanta by dad,
Don Panoz. The article quotes Indy 500 winner Parnelli Jones as
saying the Panoz is ``the great American roadster.'' Lusk fifth in
Wisconsin
</P>
<P>
   Ezra Lusk of Bainbridge finished fifth Sunday in the 250 class
of the Mazda Truck Motocross Nationals Red Bud Track 'n' Trail at
Buchanan, Wis. Jeff Emig of Riverside, Calif., won the event. Lusk,
with one victory on the 12-event series, is fifth in the point
standings with 189. Doug Henry of Oxford, Conn., leads the points
race with two victories and 243 points. The event will be broadcast
on ESPN2 at 1 p.m. July 18 and noon July 19.
</P>
<P>
   Schumachers match times
</P>
<P>
   Brothers Michael and Ralf Schumacher clocked identical times
last Friday to finish fastest on the final day of Formula One
testing for Sunday's British Grand Prix at Silverstone, near
London. Michael, in a Ferrari, and younger brother Ralf, in a
Jordan, clocked lap times of 1:24.78 on the final day of testing.
McLaren pair David Coulthard and Mika Hakkinen were left trailing
for the first time this season. They finished third and sixth
respectively. Coulthard clocked 1:25.19 and championship leader
Hakkinen 1:25.41.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
