Girls as cartoon characters with oversize shoes, tiny bodies and
huge heads. (New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) UNDATED -- July 8, 1998 -- HOME-IMPROVEMENT-B&AMP;W, 7-8 --
French polishing is a classic finishing technique developed by
French furniture makers in the early 19th century. It's a shellac
finish that's applied by rubbing the shellac onto the wood by hand.
The technique is laborious and takes time and practice to master.
Nevertheless it is an essential technique for anyone who wants to
recreate the look of authentic period furniture. (Edward R.
Lipinski/New York Times Illustration) *LITE
